{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make repeated acts of non-completion of works by tradespeople an offence",
        "additional_details": "As soon as a tradesperson starts work it is seen as them having the intention to complete and becomes a civil matter. CCJs can be hard to enforce and going to court can be costly.",
        "background": "There is not enough in place to protect vulnerable people from tradespeople who start works on their premises and fail to complete. ",
